'''人類的外貌'''是指人類[[個體|個體]]的外在[[表型|表型]]或外觀。

人類表型有無限的變異，儘管[[社會|社會]]試圖將變異性減少到不同的類別。 [[人類學|人類學]]家認為，人類的外貌，尤其是那些被認為對[[外貌吸引力|身體吸引力]]很重要的屬性，會顯著影響[[人格|人格]]和[[社會關係|社會關係]]的發展。 人類對自己的外表非常敏感（參看[[身體意象|身體意象]]等有關條目）。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Anthropological Perspectives on Physical Appearance and Body Image|url=https://modificazione.files.wordpress.com/2015/06/anthropological-perspectives-on-physical-appearance-and-body-images.pdf|last=Anderson-Fye|first=EP|date=2012|publisher=Academic Press|doi=10.1016/B978-0-12-384925-0.00003-1|editor-last=Cash|editor-first=Thomas F.|department=Body Image and Its Disorder in Anthropology|volume=1|page=19|format=PDF|quote=[Cases] of immigration have repeatedly shown that if a person who is obese believes that his or her body is beyond individual control but is placed into a medical system that assumes individual rational actors in its treatments, adherence is likely to be low and those treatments are ineffective...[Young] ethnic Fijian women associated the thin body ideal with a particular lifestyle that they found desirable|access-date=August 9, 2018|journal=|archive-date=2021-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211220035835/https://modificazione.files.wordpress.com/2015/06/anthropological-perspectives-on-physical-appearance-and-body-images.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref> 人類外表的一些差異是[[遺傳|遺傳]]的，另一些是[[人體|人體]]（身心）發展階段或狀態（如[[老化|老化]]）、[[生活型態|生活方式]]或[[疾病|疾病]]的結果，還有許多是人為修飾的結果。

有些人將一些差異與[[種族|種族]]聯繫起來，例如[[人體骨架|骨架]]形狀等。 不同的[[文化|文化]]對外貌及其對社會地位和其他現象的重視程度不同。

